id: pm-s40s
title: First-party hooks capability exemplar (lifecycle hook) for pm-izsi completion
description: "After pm-13bn (importers) and pm-bqpg (search) landed, the importers and search capabilities each have a tested first-party exemplar, but the HOOKS capability still has none (no bundled package registers before_command/after_command/on_read/on_write/on_index; the only model is the docs/SDK.md hook example + assertRegisteredHook). pm-izsi's acceptance lists importers/hooks/search, so it stays open on this. Add a safe, opt-in first-party lifecycle-hook exemplar (candidate: an on_index or after_command observability hook in an existing bundled package, or a small dedicated example) that returns deterministic no-warning output, with an assertRegisteredHook test and an SDK.md reference. Must avoid behavioral/perf regressions in auto-loaded packages (hooks run on every matching lifecycle event) — prefer a narrowly-scoped, default-inert hook. Closing this completes pm-izsi."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: "area:hooks","area:packages","area:sdk",dx,living-map
created_at: "2026-06-01T19:57:51.489Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-02T23:20:56.612Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: "Added pm-lifecycle-hooks as a default-inert hooks-only first-party package, documented the package-author exemplar map, added pm_min_version to runnable docs manifests, and updated Sentry gate expected handled Slack config filtering."
expected_result: "A safe first-party hooks exemplar exists, is tested with assertRegisteredHook, and docs point package authors to importers/hooks/search exemplars."
actual_result: pm-lifecycle-hooks registers a no-output afterCommand hook; tests and dogfood passed; Sentry/telemetry gate passed with zero relevant high/critical issues.
